---
const stats = [
  {
    value: '162',
    suffix: '',
    label: 'Regulatory Documents',
    desc: 'Spread across departmental, university, and national levels',
  },
  {
    value: '3',
    suffix: '',
    label: 'Hierarchical Levels',
    desc: 'Department › University › Council of Higher Education',
  },
  {
    value: '∞',
    suffix: '',
    label: 'Conflicts to Resolve',
    desc: 'Lower norms can override broader regulations on specific cases',
  },
];
---

<section id="problem" class="section-pad relative">
  <div class="container-x">
    <div class="reveal mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
      <div class="section-eyebrow justify-center">
        <span class="h-px w-8 bg-accent-magenta"></span>
        The Problem
      </div>
      <h2 class="section-title">
        Regulations are <span class="text-gradient-hot">scattered</span> and
        <span class="text-gradient-cool">contradictory</span>.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
        Students searching for a definitive answer must read dozens of PDFs
        across multiple authorities — and even then, conflicts between rules
        leave them guessing which one applies.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      {stats.map((s, i) => (
        <div
          class="reveal glass-card glass-card-hover group p-8"
          style={`transition-delay: ${i * 100}ms`}
        >
          <div class="font-display text-6xl font-bold text-gradient-hot">
            {s.value}{s.suffix}
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-white">
            {s.label}
          </div>
          <div class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
            {s.desc}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- Quote-style frustration card -->
    <div class="reveal mt-16 mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <div class="glass-card relative overflow-hidden p-8 sm:p-12">
        <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-20 -top-20 h-64 w-64 rounded-full bg-accent-magenta/20 blur-3xl"></div>
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent-magenta">
            Real student question
          </div>
          <blockquote class="mt-4 font-display text-2xl font-medium leading-snug text-white sm:text-3xl">
            “Which rule wins — the department's internship guideline, the
            university's general regulation, or the YÖK directive?”
          </blockquote>
          <div class="mt-6 text-sm text-slate-400">
            Without a system that understands legal hierarchy, the answer is
            buried in 200+ pages of dense Turkish legalese.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
